The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Bengal | Briefs
                                                                                                                     4                                                                                      BRIEFS
                  
	Calcutta, Dec.11: A jackal was spotted on a runway of Calcutta airport this evening, delaying flights for over an hour and a half from 5.30pm.    
	Officials said an IndiGo flight from Delhi had to hover for 20 minutes and a JetLite plane about to take off had to be halted. Air services could resume only around 7pm.         
	Calcutta: A Howrah youth, believed to be mentally unstable, has been held for sending obscene emails to a mobile company, using the name of a woman. Arup Karmakar, a former employee of the company, wanted to harass his colleague after she spurned his advances, police said. Earlier, he was arrested for sending an email threatening to blow up the Dakhineswar temple.                                                                                                                                                      
